:+1: 
Please also provide annotation for uniqueness constraint as a model `convention`, so we don't have to "drop down" to [manual model builder](https://github.com/aspnet/EntityFramework/pull/866#issuecomment-98000296) `configuration` probably like so:

``` c#
[Unique]
public int MySurrogateKey { get; set; }
// here MySurrogateKey can be null as a unique value
```

``` c#
[UniqueNotNull]
public int MySurrogateKey { get; set; }
// here MySurrogateKey can not be null
```

``` c#
[UniqueAllowNull]
public int MySurrogateKey { get; set; }
// here MySurrogateKey can be null multiple times, but non-null values should be unique
```

